headline: Häagen-Dazs, Starbucks Mull Overhauls in China to Fend Off Powerful Local Rivals
summary: (Bloomberg) -- The consumer landscape in China was very different in the 1990s, when Häagen-Dazs and Starbucks ventured in with premium products that were alien to most people. They made huge inroads nonetheless, opening outlets at breakneck pace and raking in revenue. But times are changing, and they, like many other Western brands, are reassessing their approach to the world’s second-biggest economy, including possibly selling their businesses. headline: Goldman Sachs Raises Starbucks (SBUX) PT to $95, Turnaround Strategy Gains Clarity
